# Solving the `map_id` proof for `Hom_c_?` in Lean 4

We need to prove that `map_id (X : α)` for `Hom_c_?` is equal to `rfl`.
The definition of `map_id` is `fun g => comp (id X) g`.
The definition of `id` in the context of `Hom` is `fun x => x`.
So, `comp (id X) g` becomes `comp (fun x => x) g`.
The definition of `comp` is `fun f g => f ≫ g`.
So, `comp (fun x => x) g` becomes `(fun x => x) ≫ g`.
The definition of `≫` (composition of arrows) is `fun f g => g ∘ f`.
So, `(fun x => x) ≫ g` becomes `g ∘ (fun x => x)`.
The definition of `∘` (composition of functions) is `fun f g => fun x => f (g x)`.
So, `g ∘ (fun x => x)` becomes `fun x => g (x)`.
This is exactly the definition of `id` applied to `g`.
So, `fun g => comp (id X) g` is equal to `fun g => g`.
This means `map_id (X : α)` is `rfl`.

